President Obama expresses his gratitude and praise for Admiral Thad Allen's service, particularly his leadership during the BP Oil Spill response effort. Despite being eligible for retirement, Admiral Allen chose to serve his country when his skills and experience were urgently needed. The President acknowledges that the success of the response effort would not have been possible without Admiral Allen's leadership. As the administration continues its work to assist the Gulf Coast, they will continue to benefit from Admiral Allen's selfless service and dedicated leadership. President Obama wishes him well in his future endeavors.